[[File:AshmoreandCartierIslands.png|thumb|Ashmore and Cartier Islands]]
The '''Territory of Ashmore and Cartier Islands'''<ref name="Agency2010">{{cite book|author=The Central Intelligence Agency|title=The World Factbook|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m-9eSrZtYAAC&pg=PA39|year=2010|publisher=Potomac Books, Inc.|isbn=978-1-59797-541-4|page=39}}</ref> is an uninhabited [[States and territories of Australia|external territory]]<ref>{{cite book | url=http://www.alrc.gov.au/publications/alrc-80-legal-risk-international-transactions/10-external-territories?print | title=Legal Risk in International Transactions (ALRC Report 80) | year=2006 | isbn=0642254877 | chapter=10: External territories | publisher=Australian Law Reform Commission (ALRC), Australian Government | accessdate=2014-04-14 }}</ref> of [[Australia]] consisting of four low-lying tropical islands in two separate [[reef]]s, and the {{convert|12|nmi|adj=on}} [[Territorial waters|territorial sea]] generated by the islands.<ref name=DIRD/> The territory is located in the [[Indian Ocean]] situated on the edge of the [[continental shelf]], about {{convert|320|km|0|abbr=on}} off the northwest coast of Australia and {{convert|144|km|0|abbr=on}} south of the [[Indonesia]]n island of [[Rote Island|Rote]].<ref name=DIRD>{{cite web | url=http://www.regional.gov.au/territories/ashmore_cartier/index.aspx | accessdate=2014-04-14 | date=2014-01-29 | work=Territories of Australia | publisher=Department of the Infrastructure and Regional Development, Australian Government | title=Ashmore and Cartier Islands }}</ref>

Ashmore Reef is called ''Pulau Pasir'' by Indonesians and ''Nusa Solokaek'' in the [[Rotenese language]]. Both names have the meaning "sand island".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://rspas.anu.edu.au/people/personal/foxxj_rspas/Fishermen_MOU_BOX.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060827142957/http://rspas.anu.edu.au/people/personal/foxxj_rspas/Fishermen_MOU_BOX.pdf |archivedate=2006-08-27 |title=A STUDY OF SOCIO-ECONOMIC ISSUES FACING TRADITIONAL INDONESIAN FISHERS WHO ACCESS THE MOU BOX}}</ref>

{{See also|Birds of Ashmore Reef|Flora of Ashmore and Cartier Islands}}
[[File:Cartier Island.png|thumb|right|Cartier Island and surrounding reef ([[NASA]] satellite image)]]

*The [[Ashmore Reef Marine Park]] and [[Cartier Island Marine Park]] are both classed as strict nature reserves (IUCN Ia) and protect biodiverse areas of significant and international importance, as well as cultural heritage.

